  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Priyansh, I noticed how well you formed your questions using 'do' last time. That was a big win! What's on your mind today?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Thanks, Maya! I'm feeling more confident now. Today, I want to talk about how to describe my new startup idea in English. Also, maybe we can practice talking about future plans?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "That sounds exciting. Startup ideas are fun to discuss. What problem does your idea solve?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "My startup is about helping small businesses go digital. Many local shops still use paper records, which is slow. We’ll give them a simple app for inventory and sales. It’s like *chaat*—quick and easy for them. How would you say that in natural English?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "That’s a great idea — quick and easy for local shops. The phrasing you used is clear! If you want to sound even smoother, you could say, “We’re building a simple app to help small businesses go digital, just like *chaat* — quick and easy.” Does that sound good to you?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Yeah, that sounds good! I like the word \"smooth.\" Can I use \"just like chaat\" in a presentation? Also, how do I talk about future plans like \"we will launch\" or \"we plan to\"?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You can definitely say \"just like chaat\" — it adds a nice, relatable touch. For future plans, \"we will launch\" is straightforward. If you want to sound a bit more natural, you could say, \"We plan to launch next month\" or \"We’re aiming to launch by the end of the year.\" Which one do you prefer?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I think \"We plan to launch next month\" sounds better for a presentation — it feels confident but not too rigid. What if I want to mention future growth? Like, \"we want to expand to other cities\"? Is there a smoother way to say that?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Got it — \"We plan to launch next month\" sounds confident and natural. For future growth, you could say, \"We aim to expand to other cities\" or \"We’re looking to grow to other cities.\" Both sound professional. What’s your timeline for expansion?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Honestly, the timeline is still early — maybe six months after the launch. I want to make sure the app is stable first. But I can say, \"We aim to expand after the initial launch once the app is stable.\" Does that flow well?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Yes, that flows well. It shows thoughtfulness. You could also say, \"We plan to expand after the app is stable and running smoothly.\" Both versions work. How do you want to describe the app’s stability?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Stable and running smoothly\" sounds good — maybe add something about customer feedback? Like, \"once we get feedback and improve\"? Or is that too much?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Yes, that works — it shows you care about improvement. You could say, \"We plan to expand after the app is stable, running smoothly, and we’ve incorporated customer feedback.\" It’s clear and adds a professional touch. What’s your next step before the launch?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Our next step is to finish the beta testing — we’re working with five local shops to test the app. I can say, \"We’re currently in beta testing with five local businesses to ensure everything works well.\" Does that sound okay?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "That sounds good — clear and natural. You could also say, \"We’re in the final stages of beta testing with five local businesses to make sure everything runs smoothly.\" Both versions sound strong. What’s your goal for the beta testing?"
    }
  ],
